records.addlTxt:
Sentencing proceeded. Statements made as to sentencing. State has complied with victim notification. 

As to COUNT 1 as AMENDED:
Court ordered defendant to serve 1 YEAR in the House of Correction credit for 69 days time served.

Court STAYED the sentence and placed defendant on probation for 2 YEARS. If revoked, defendant is allowed release for HOC programs and HOC work opportunities, and release for school if already enrolled prior to being revoked. 

Conditions of probation: 
1) Court ordered 5 MONTHS of condition time in the House of Correction; this is STAYED to be used at the discretion of the agent;
2) Enroll in GED/HSED program full time, or be employed at full time job (40 hours per week);
3) AODA assessment;
4) Participate in a parenting class;
5) Maintain absolute sobriety, absolutely no drugs or alcohol;
6) If defendant is prescribed any medication, he is to inform the agent BEFORE getting the prescription filled;
7) Continue taking ADHD medication as ordered; Defendant is to provide name of doctor and a phone number to agent;
8) No contact with the victim;
9) Defendant is not to use any type of social media; If defendant possesses a smartphone, computer, or any other electronic device with access to social media, it is to be made available for the agent to inspect at any time;
10) Provide DNA sample and pay DNA surcharge;
11) Pay all mandatory costs, fees and surcharges during period of probation. Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment;
12) Comply with all rules as set forth by agent;

Bail on deposit to be applied towards costs, fees and surcharges.

Upon successful completion of conditions of probation, Court will allow for expungment of conviction in this matter. 

Court set restitution at ZERO. 

Appellate rights notice given to the defendant. 
Filed;
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief;
signed Ineligible Voting Notice & Acknowledgement;
Pretrial Incarceration Credit.
